@page "/customers"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>Customers &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="500+ revenue teams across the Americas use NavTour to turn buyer curiosity into closed deals. Read how P4 Warehouse, Barrdega, and CifraHQ run their demo motions." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Customers</span>
        <h1>500+ teams running demos<br />that <em>actually close deals.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">From Panama City to Buenos Aires, revenue teams across 32 countries use NavTour to replace the "can you send a deck?" with an interactive product experience.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">Talk to the team</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@* ── STATS ── *@
<div class="nt-results">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <div class="nt-stats">
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Teams using NavTour</div>
                <div class="n">500<span class="sym">+</span></div>
                <p>Revenue teams across sales, marketing, pre-sales, and customer success.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Countries</div>
                <div class="n">32</div>
                <p>Americas-native, bilingual EN/ES, deployed across 32 countries.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Demo-to-opp lift</div>
                <div class="n">+47<span class="sym">%</span></div>
                <p>Median lift in demo-to-opportunity conversion. Medians, not best case.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-stat">
                <div class="lbl">Time saved</div>
                <div class="n">6<span class="sym">h</span></div>
                <p>Per rep, per week &mdash; pre-call discovery and post-call follow-ups, automated.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

@* ── CASE STUDY 1 ── *@
<section class="nt-frames-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <span class="eyebrow">Case study &middot; P4 Warehouse</span>
                <h3>From &ldquo;can you send a recording?&rdquo;<br />to <em>self-serve demo hubs.</em></h3>
                <p>P4 Warehouse&rsquo;s pre-sales team was spending 3 hours per deal building custom screen recordings for each ops persona. NavTour replaced the recordings with a self-serve hub — one per vertical, always current.</p>
                <div style="margin-top:24px;padding:20px 24px;background:var(--nt-bg-alt);border-radius:12px;border-left:3px solid var(--nt-orange)">
                    <blockquote style="margin:0;font-style:italic;color:var(--nt-ink);font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.6">
                        &ldquo;NavTour replaced four tools in our sales stack &mdash; and our SDRs finally stopped asking marketing for &lsquo;the updated demo link.&rsquo; It just lives in the hub, always fresh, always branded.&rdquo;
                    </blockquote>
                    <cite style="display:block;margin-top:12px;font-style:normal;font-size:0.88rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--nt-muted)">
                        <b style="color:var(--nt-ink)">Mar&iacute;a Vel&aacute;squez</b> &middot; VP Revenue Ops, P4 Warehouse &middot; Panama City
                    </cite>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top:20px;display:flex;gap:40px">
                    <div><div style="font-size:2rem;font-family:var(--nt-display);font-weight:700;color:var(--nt-ink)">2.4&times;</div><div style="font-size:0.82rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--nt-muted)">Demo-to-meeting rate</div></div>
                    <div><div style="font-size:2rem;font-family:var(--nt-display);font-weight:700;color:var(--nt-ink)">40%</div><div style="font-size:0.82rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--nt-muted)">Less time on discovery calls</div></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">P4 Warehouse &middot; demo hub</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/hub.png" alt="P4 Warehouse demo hub" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row reverse">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <span class="eyebrow">Case study &middot; CifraHQ</span>
                <h3>Onboarding that doesn&rsquo;t need<br /><em>a CSM in the room.</em></h3>
                <p>CifraHQ&rsquo;s customer success team was running 8-session onboarding sprints for every new customer. After building a NavTour library for each workflow module, they cut their onboarding call load by 60% in the first quarter.</p>
                <div style="margin-top:24px;padding:20px 24px;background:var(--nt-bg-alt);border-radius:12px;border-left:3px solid var(--nt-orange)">
                    <blockquote style="margin:0;font-style:italic;color:var(--nt-ink);font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.6">
                        &ldquo;Our customers complete onboarding at midnight if that&rsquo;s when they have time. The tour library means we spend CSM time on strategy, not feature walkthroughs.&rdquo;
                    </blockquote>
                    <cite style="display:block;margin-top:12px;font-style:normal;font-size:0.88rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.04em;color:var(--nt-muted)">
                        <b style="color:var(--nt-ink)">Roberto Cifuentes</b> &middot; Head of Customer Success, CifraHQ &middot; Bogot&aacute;
                    </cite>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top:20px;display:flex;gap:40px">
                    <div><div style="font-size:2rem;font-family:var(--nt-display);font-weight:700;color:var(--nt-ink)">60%</div><div style="font-size:0.82rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--nt-muted)">Fewer onboarding calls</div></div>
                    <div><div style="font-size:2rem;font-family:var(--nt-display);font-weight:700;color:var(--nt-ink)">72%</div><div style="font-size:0.82rem;font-family:var(--nt-mono);letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--nt-muted)">Step completion rate</div></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">CifraHQ &middot; onboarding library</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/player-step1.png" alt="CifraHQ self-serve onboarding tour" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

